    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Banská Štiavnica Town Council (Kremnica, 17
                    February 1541)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He has heard that they have captured a certain Martinus Zybolent, who
                            declared himself a serf of Várday, and that his hearing will be held
                            tomorrow. Allegedly there are some credible witnesses whose testimony
                            will be enough the exonerate him or at least reduce the sentence. He
                            asks that the witnesses are allowed in and to grant their request to
                            testify. And if the sentence is harsher, it should be reduced at his and
                            Várday’s request.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Salutem et mei commendationem, Prudentes et Circumspecti Domini et
                    Amici Honorandissimi!</p>
                <p>Intelligo quendam <persName>Martinum Zybolen</persName>,<note
                        type="critic">We do not know him more closely.</note> qui se in colonum
                    reverendissimi domini nostri <persName>Strigoniensis</persName><note
                        type="critic">Pál Várday.</note> iamdudum addixisse dicitur, apud
                    Dominationes Vestras captum esse, et die crastina iudicium in ipsius causa per
                    easdem fieri. Dicitur autem nonnullos fidedignos testes habere, quorum
                    attestationes in sublevamen immo potius in liberationem causae ipsius plurimum
                    facerent. Quare rogo Dominationes Vestras, velint testes ipsius
                        <persName>Martini Zybolen</persName> admittere examinareque et quatenus
                    aequitas postulaverit eis locum dare. Etsi etiam aliquid gravius contra ipsum
                        <persName>Martinum</persName> colonum adductum praefati reverendissimi
                    domini nostri <persName>Strigoniensis</persName> ius ferre videretur, tum ipsius
                    reverendissimi domini <persName>Strigoniensis</persName> boni patroni
                    Dominationum Vestrarum, tum meae petitionis intuitu, ita moderare iudicium et
                    sententiam ipsam velint, ut et ipsius domini <persName>Strigoniensis</persName>
                    et meae petitionis respectus <del corresp="Olahus">aliquis</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">aliquid</add> habitus <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >esse</del> a Dominationibus Vestris esse videatur. Quod ipse dominus
                        <persName>Strigoniensis</persName> omni patrocinio suo, ego vero meis
                    officiis ab Dominationibus Vestris promerebimur. Dominationes Vestras feliciter
                    valere opto, quibus me commendo. </p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Cremnicio</placeName> 17. Februarii 1541. </p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Nicolaus Olahus custos Albensis consiliarius regius
                        etc.</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Prudentibus et circumspectis iudici et iuratis civibus civitatis
                    Schemniciensis etc. dominis et amicis honorandissimis. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
